body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our support team at Dream Motors. My name is Kyle Davis. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great to meet you, Natalie. How can I assist you today? Could you provide me with your phone number so I can locate your account in our system?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five, two zero zero, one zero zero eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Natalie. And can you also provide me with your email address to ensure smooth communication in resolving your issue?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is natalie.davis@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Natalie. I will now review your billing concern. Your enthusiasm is appreciated. Let's work together to find a solution that will satisfy your needs.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm looking forward to resolving this, Kyle.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I appreciate your patience, Natalie. Thank you for your time and cooperation. Should you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a wonderful day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Kyle. Have a great day too.
